Topic	Meaning
Unit Testing	Testing a small, independent part of code
Good Unit Test	Fast, independent, repeatable, readable, deterministic
What to Test	Business logic, boundaries, errors, invalid inputs
What Not to Test	Framework functionality and trivial implementation details
Test Naming	Clearly describes method, condition, and expected result
AAA Pattern	Arrange → Act → Assert
Black-Box Testing	Testing input/output without knowing internal implementation
SetUp	Runs before every test
TearDown	Runs after every test
Parameterized Test	Same test with multiple input values
Ignoring Tests	Temporarily skips a test
Trustworthy Tests	Tests that provide reliable confidence in software behavior